name: State Bird Provisions
description: An inventive, high-energy spot known for serving small plates dim-sum style from carts. Famous for their fried state bird with onion jam.

name: Zuni Caf√©
description: A legendary San Francisco institution famous for its wood-fired brick oven and iconic roasted chicken with warm bread salad.

name: Delfina
description: A vibrant Mission District favorite serving farm-to-table Italian fare. Their spaghetti with plum tomatoes and garlic is a masterclass in simplicity.

name: Nopa
description: A bustling North of the Panhandle spot specializing in organic wood-fired cuisine and one of the city's most celebrated burgers.

name: Kokkari Estiatorio
description: An upscale rustic Greek restaurant that feels like a cozy Mediterranean inn. The grilled lamb chops are legendary.

name: Mister Jiu's
description: A Michelin-starred contemporary Chinese restaurant in the heart of Chinatown, blending traditional flavors with local Californian ingredients.

name: Liholiho Yacht Club
description: A high-energy Heritage-driven restaurant serving food inspired by Hawaii, India, and China. Don't miss the tuna poke on nori crackers.

name: Tartine Manufactory
description: A massive, airy complex housing a legendary bakery, restaurant, and coffee shop. Famous for their incredible sourdough and seasonal toasts.
